# GameNative — Player Profile Fix + In-Game Chat Panel + Game Invites

## What is broken right now (from screenshot)

The current friend profile screen shows:
- A plain card with avatar, name, "Offline" text
- "Games / Recently played · By hours" label with "Loading..." text that never loads
- A single oversized bright blue "Message" pill button
- The rest of the screen is completely empty black space

This must be completely replaced. Every section below is required.

---

## CRITICAL NAVIGATION RULE

When a user taps any friend row in the friends list, they MUST go to
PlayerProfileScreen — NOT ChatScreen. Chat is only reachable by pressing
the Message button inside the profile screen.

Find the friends list onFriendClick / onItemClick lambda and change it to:
```kotlin
onFriendClick = { friend ->
    navController.navigate("playerProfile/${friend.steamId}")
}
```

Do NOT navigate directly to chat from the friends list anywhere.

