## PART 1 — PlayerProfileScreen.kt (full replacement)

### Screen structure top to bottom

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  HERO SECTION (full bleed, 220dp tall)              │
│  Game art background OR atmospheric glow            │
│  Avatar + name + presence + status overlaid         │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  ACTION BUTTONS ROW (Message | Invite | More)       │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  CURRENTLY PLAYING CARD (only if InGame)            │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  GAMES SECTION HEADER + sort chips                  │
│  LazyColumn of game rows sorted by playtime desc    │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Data model

```kotlin
data class FriendProfile(
    val steamId: String,
    val displayName: String,
    val avatarUrl: String,
    val presenceState: PresenceState,  // ONLINE, OFFLINE, IN_GAME, AWAY
    val currentGameName: String?,      // null when not playing
    val currentGameAppId: Int?,
    val currentGameHeaderUrl: String?, // cdn.../{appId}/header.jpg
    val statusMessage: String?,
    val memberSince: String?
)

data class FriendGame(
    val appId: Int,
    val name: String,
    val headerUrl: String,             // 460x215
    val capsuleUrl: String,            // 600x900
    val playtimeForever: Int,          // total minutes — SORT BY THIS descending
    val playtime2Weeks: Int,           // recent minutes
    val lastPlayed: Long?              // unix timestamp
)

enum class PresenceState { ONLINE, OFFLINE, IN_GAME, AWAY }
```

